Title : Douglas L. Peterson
Text : {{Use mdy dates|date=May 2014}}
[[File:Fullsizedouglas peterson.jpg|thumb|Peterson in 2013]]
'''Douglas L. Peterson''' is the chief executive officer of [[S&P Global]]<ref name="auto1">{{cite web|url=http://investor.spglobal.com/CustomPage/Index?KeyGenPage=326507&bio=Douglas_L+_Peterson|title=Operating Committee - S&P Global|website=Investor.spglobal.com|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref> (NYSE:  SPGI)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nyse.com/quote/XNYS:SPGI|title=NYSE|website=Nyse.com|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>, formerly McGraw Hill Financial. He became president and chief executive officer in November 2013. Peterson has served on S&P Globalâ€™s Board of Directors since July 2013.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://investor.spglobal.com/file/Index?KeyFile=18160595|title=News Release - S&P Global|website=Investor.spglobal.com|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref> He originally joined the company as president of Standard & Poor's Ratings Services in 2011.<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2011/08/23/s-p-s-new-president-a-crisis-troubleshooter/|title=S.&P.'s New President, a Crisis Troubleshooter|first=Michael J. de la|last=Merced|website=DealBook.nytimes.com|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=b0904df0-0ae0-11e9-940a-71adfa3faf1d&url=L3Jlc2VhcmNoL3N0b2Nrcy9wZW9wbGUvcGVyc29uLmFzcD9wZXJzb25JZD05OTY1MzY4JnByaXZjYXBJZD0yMTcxOQ==|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=Bloomberg.com|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>

==Education==
Peterson was raised in Santa Fe, New Mexico, and earned his [[MBA]] from the [[Wharton School]] at the [[University of Pennsylvania]] in 1985.<ref name="bloomberg.com">{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/tosv2.html?vid=&uuid=b10f9010-0ae0-11e9-8026-fdbb92e011d7&url=L3Jlc2VhcmNoL3N0b2Nrcy9wZW9wbGUvcGVyc29uLmFzcD9wZXJzb25JZD05OTY1MzY4JnRpY2tlcj1D|title=Bloomberg - Are you a robot?|website=Bloomberg.com|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>

==Citigroup==
Peterson worked for [[Citigroup]] for 26 years. From 2004 to 2010 Peterson was the CEO of Citigroup Japan. He served as chief auditor of Citigroup from 2001 to 2004. Other positions within Citigroup include serving as country manager for Uruguay and Costa Rica.{{year needed|date=December 2018}}<ref name="auto"/><ref name="bloomberg.com"/> Peterson also served as chief operating officer of Citibank.

==S&P Global==
Peterson is a member of the board of directors of S&P Global and the Institute of International Finance's Market Monitoring Group. He has also served on the [[Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation]]'s Systemic Resolution Advisory Committee for over two years. Peterson serves on the boards of advisors for the Wharton Financial Institutions Center, as well as the Kravis Leadership Institute and the Partnership for New York City. Peterson is a member of the boards of trustees for [[Claremont McKenna College]] and is also on the board for Paul Taylor Dance Company.<ref name="auto1"/>

==Personal==
Peterson is married and has two sons.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cmc.edu/news/does-it-surprise-you-that-sps-new-president-happens-to-be-a-claremont-mckenna-alumnus|title=Does It Surprise You That S&P's New President Happens to be a Claremont McKenna Alumnus?|website=Cmc.edu|accessdate=December 28, 2018}}</ref>

